verbs.description: forelive (third-person singular simple present forelives, present participle foreliving, simple past and past participle forelived)

entries.meaning: To live or come before; precede
examples: […]  Or if I seek the visitation, then He fills me, and my foul is carried on, And then do I forelive the race of men, So that the things that will be, are to me  […]
